giggle /ˈɡɪɡəl/

(giggling,giggled,giggles) 

1. V-T/V-I If someone giggles , they laugh in a childlike way, because they are amused, nervous, or embarrassed. 咯咯地笑 

例： Both girls began to giggle. 两个女孩都咯咯地笑起来。 

例： 'I beg your pardon?' she giggled. “对不起，你说什么？”她咯咯地笑着问。 

2. N-COUNT Giggle is also a noun. 咯咯的笑 

例： She gave a little giggle. 她咯咯地笑了一下。 

3. N-PLURAL If you say that someone has the giggles , you mean they cannot stop giggling. 咯咯笑个不止 

例： I was so nervous I got the giggles. 我紧张得咯咯笑个不止。

